# The Rise of Data-Centric AI

For many years, researchers followed a model-centric approach.

When performance was poor, the solution was:

```text
Poor Accuracy
      ↓
Bigger Model
      ↓
More Layers
      ↓
More Complexity
```

Today, the industry increasingly follows a different philosophy.

This philosophy is called:

# Data-Centric AI

Data-Centric AI focuses on improving:

* Data quality
* Label quality
* Data consistency
* Dataset coverage
* Data collection processes

instead of endlessly modifying models.

Visualization:

```text
Traditional Approach

Poor Results
      ↓
Change Model
      ↓
Change Model Again
      ↓
Change Model Again


Modern Approach

Poor Results
      ↓
Inspect Data
      ↓
Fix Labels
      ↓
Improve Coverage
      ↓
Improve Quality
```

This shift has become one of the most important trends in modern AI development.

---

# Real Industry Perspective

Many beginners imagine AI projects look like this:

```text
10% Data
90% Model Building
```

Reality is almost the opposite.

A typical industry project often looks like:

```text
Data Collection
        30%

Data Cleaning
        25%

EDA
        15%

Feature Engineering
        15%

Model Development
        10%

Deployment
         5%
```

Notice something surprising.

The actual model may consume less than 10% of the project's effort.

The majority of work happens before training even begins.

This is why Data Engineering exists as a separate discipline.

