# Key Takeaways

* Data is the foundation of every AI system.
* Machine Learning learns patterns from data, not intelligence.
* Poor-quality data leads to poor-quality predictions.
* Data-centric AI focuses on improving data rather than endlessly changing models.
* Raw data is messy but valuable.
* Structured data is highly organized and easy to analyze.
* Semi-structured data provides flexibility while maintaining organization.
* Unstructured data contains most of the world's information but requires additional processing.
* Understanding data is the first step toward becoming a Data Engineer, ML Engineer, or Data Scientist.

